title: Baseball Stadiums
name: Baseball Stadiums
description:
A Map by Jknigh17

These are the baseball stadiums I have visited in my 19 years of existence. They are not necesarily in order of least to most favorite, but all are extraordinary.

properties.description: Posted by Jknigh17Where we are now is called Dolphins Stadium, this is where both the Florida Marlins and the Miami Dolphins play. I watched a Florida Marlins vs. Colorado Rockies game here.
Posted by Jknigh17This is Tropicana Field, home of the Tampa Bay Devil Rays. I mainly visit this stadium when I am visiting my relatives down in Tampa.
Posted by Jknigh17This is the famous location of the Arizona Diamondbacks, former World Champs. I visited this stadium when it was first opened!
Posted by Jknigh17This is Turner Field, home of the Atlanta Braves. I have visited this stadium the most of all due to the fact that it is the closest to home.
Posted by Jknigh17The Anaheim Angels Stadium. One of the most beautiful of all MLB stadiums. This was one of the first staiums I visited with my family.
Posted by Jknigh17I have visited this stadium as well. This is where the LA Dodgers play. Me and my family hit up almost all of the baseball stadiums in SW California.
Posted by Jknigh17This is the home of the cursed Chicago Cubs. Wrigley Field is also unique, mainly because of its ivy walls in the outfield. Go and see it for yourself!

Posted by Jknigh17This is the historical Fenway Park. I visited this stadium on a school orchesra trip. This stadium is amazing and rich in history. Also, it has the biggest wall in left field..."THE GREEN MONSTER"

Posted by Jknigh17This is where the Minnesota Twins play their baseball games. This stadium was just like Tropicana Field, becuase it was a dome.They did have good ice cream, I got it in a Twins helmet.
Posted by Jknigh17This is the location of Safeco Field, home of the Seattle Mariners. I liked this stadium a lot and often wear the hat I purchased from there.
